snippet.textDisplay:
Original national anthem of Pakistan was written by Pandit Jagannath at the behest of Jinnah. He did this overnight. This was however discarded after Jinnah and new anthem written by Hafiz Jalandhari was taken. First was by a Pakistani Hindu and the second was by an Indian Muslim.
However, the present anthem has all Persian words and only "ka" is one word of Sanskrit taken in Urdu.
snippet.textOriginal:
Original national anthem of Pakistan was written by Pandit Jagannath at the behest of Jinnah. He did this overnight. This was however discarded after Jinnah and new anthem written by Hafiz Jalandhari was taken. First was by a Pakistani Hindu and the second was by an Indian Muslim.
However, the present anthem has all Persian words and only "ka" is one word of Sanskrit taken in Urdu.
